    <briefdescription>
<para>API for <bold><computeroutput>touch input device</computeroutput></bold> object. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>LameUI does NOT have its own Touch Input driver. User must supply their own functions to read touch input. Touch input data is stored in <computeroutput>lui_touch_input_data_t</computeroutput>: <programlisting filename=".C"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">typedef</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">struct<sp/></highlight><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="struct__lui__touch__input__data__s" kindref="compound">_lui_touch_input_data_s</ref></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>uint8_t<sp/><ref refid="struct__lui__touch__input__data__s_1afb1054eabf8033209df3b6bc2ca5a2af" kindref="member">is_pressed</ref>;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>int16_t<sp/><ref refid="struct__lui__touch__input__data__s_1a7f21ada3a9a2b790c51c2f767ea3e30e" kindref="member">x</ref>;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>int16_t<sp/><ref refid="struct__lui__touch__input__data__s_1a0dda12587fe70222aa328760a1ab2055" kindref="member">y</ref>;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}<ref refid="lame__ui_8h_1aa6d259bd0bdabcea1b151e6ae903b135" kindref="member">lui_touch_input_data_t</ref>;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>When touch input is NOT pressed, x and y value must be -1.</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
